*****************************************************************
Please add the following to your apache config, and restart.

#
# Directives to allow use of AWStats as a CGI
#
Alias /awstatsclasses "%%WWWDIR%%/classes/"
Alias /awstatscss "%%WWWDIR%%/css/"
Alias /awstatsicons "%%WWWDIR%%/icons/"
ScriptAlias /awstats/ "%%WWWDIR%%/cgi-bin/"

#
# This is to permit URL access to scripts/files in AWStats directory.
#
<Directory "%%WWWDIR%%/">
    Options None
    AllowOverride None
    Order allow,deny
    Allow from all
</Directory>

*****************************************************************

If you are upgrading from AWStats 6.4 or older, please note the following:

If you used the geoip plugin, you must edit your AWStats config file
to change the line
 LoadPlugin="geoip GEOIP_STANDARD"
into
 LoadPlugin="geoip GEOIP_STANDARD /pathto/GeoIP.dat"

*****************************************************************
